stories.text:
I love low level kernel/OS stuff but loathe the operating systems we have today. Windows, Linux, and BSD's designed are heavily rooted in principles we designed 30+ years ago. These weren't designed with the requirements we have today - like configuration management for servers, live security upgrades, mitigating CPU flaws.

I want to see something radically different. Whether it's for desktops or microcontrollers I don't mind.

I'm aware of a few hobby projects such as SerenityOS which are cool but still very 'inside the box' in terms of design and don't really have any backing.
